"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142367","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-03","<p>We respect the right of Foreign and Commonwealth Heads of Mission serving in the UK to pursue their own State's priorities in the same way that we expect British Heads of Mission overseas to be able to pursue the UK's priorities.</p><p>Promoting and defending human rights is a fundamental part of the UK's foreign policy. Working with other countries, whether overseas or in the UK, is an essential element in meeting our human rights goals. Where the UK has concerns, we will engage both through our network of posts and with their representatives in the UK.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-09-03T10:35:22.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142367/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142367/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-07-25","Diplomatic Service: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans he has to ensure that ambassadors to the UK prioritise human rights issues.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","282231"
