"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141645","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-09-09","<p>In the last three years the Medical Research Council has funded one project relevant to mindfulness-based therapies. £149k was awarded in 2018 to researchers based at the University of Bristol for two years to evaluate a multi-stage intervention to improve foster carers mental health and well-being.</p><p> </p><p>The number of applications and success rates for projects relevant to mindfulness-based therapies cannot be provided. All applications to UK Research and Innovation are submitted in confidence and when research topics are specialised in nature, releasing information on the number of applications may result in Research Organisations and applicants potentially being identified.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-09-09T13:35:36.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141645/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141645/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-07-24","Mental Health Services: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many applications for research into mindfulness-based therapies were (a) accepted and (b) rejected by the Medical Research Council in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","281632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141646","Department for Education","false","2019-09-03","<p>The Government has accepted the School Teachers' Review Body’s recommendations in full to uplift the minima and maxima of all pay ranges and allowances by 2.75%. To help schools implement the teachers’ pay award, the Department for Education is investing an additional £105 million into the existing Teachers’ Pay Grant this financial year. This is on top of the £321 million funding that schools are receiving this year to implement the residual 2018/19 pay award.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-09-03T11:49:34.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141646/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1141646/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-07-24","Teachers: Pay Settlements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Written Statement of 22 July 2019, HCWS1766 on Teachers update, whether the £105 million is additional funding from the public purse.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","281772"
